{"word":"H6504 - פָּרַד - pârad - paw-rad' - Disperse","slug":"H6504","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">פָּרַד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>pârad"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>paw-rad'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Disperse"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E4;&#x05BC;&#x05E8;&#x05D3; - pa&#x0302;rad</b> - <i>paw-rad'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>break</i> through, that is, <i>spread</i> or <i>separate</i> (oneself): - disperse, divide, be out of joint, part, scatter (abroad), separate (self), sever self, stretch, sunder."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6507\">H6507</a>, <a href=\"#/H6514\">H6514</a>"}]}